4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LOCAL BOARD OF HEALTH POWERS RELATED TO
5 ISOLATION AND QUARANTINE ORDERS; PROHIBITING A LOCAL BOARD OF HEALTH FROM
6 REQUIRING A VACCINATION OR OTHER MEDICATION AS A CONDITION OF RELEASE FROM AN
7 ISOLATION OR QUARANTINE ORDER; PROVIDING AN APPROPRIATION; AMENDING SECTION 50-2-
8 116, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 50-2-116, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "50-2-116. Powers and duties of local boards of health. (1) Except as provided in subsection (5),
14 in order to carry out the purposes of the public health system, in collaboration with federal, state, and local
15 partners, each local board of health shall:
16 (a) recommend to the governing body the appointment of a local health officer who is:
17 (i) a physician;
18 (ii) a person with a master's degree in public health; or
19 (iii) a person with equivalent education and experience, as determined by the department;
20 (b) elect a presiding officer and other necessary officers;
21 (c) adopt bylaws to govern meetings;
22 (d) hold regular meetings at least quarterly and hold special meetings as necessary;
23 (e) identify, assess, prevent, and ameliorate conditions of public health importance through:
24 (i) epidemiological tracking and investigation;
25 (ii) screening and testing;
26 (iii) isolation and quarantine measures;
27 (iv) diagnosis, treatment, and case management;
28 (v) abatement of public health nuisances;
