17 necessary regulations that are not less stringent than state standards for the control and disposal of sewage
18 from private and public buildings and facilities that are not regulated by Title 75, chapter 6, or Title 76, chapter
19 4. The regulations must describe standards for granting variances from the minimum requirements that are
20 identical to standards promulgated by the department of environmental quality and must provide for appeal of
21 variance decisions to the department of environmental quality as required by 75-5-305. If the local board of
22 health regulates or permits water well drilling, the regulations must prohibit the drilling of a well if the well
23 isolation zone, as defined in 76-4-102, encroaches onto adjacent private property without the authorization of
24 the private property owner.
